<bug>
    <id>14219</id>
    <title>Graph API returns wrong like count</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">Graph API says our page (http://bzzabout.it/76) has 46 likes which is incorrect.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.2">Yet_ the Like button for this page and the Old REST API says the page has 922 likes which is correct.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">Like Button: http://bzzabout.it/76
Graph API: http://graph.facebook.com/http://bzzabout.it/76
Old REST API: http://api.facebook.com/restserver.php?method=links.getStats&amp;urls=http://bzzabout.it/76</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">Please fix this ASAP.</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.2">This is occuring across hundreds of our clients  pages and severely affecting our business!</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.3">And this is only the latest in a series of issues for us involving the new Graph API.</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.4">In fact we reported a similar bug just a couple of months ago involving the same page.</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.5">The old REST API does not seem to have these kind of problems_ should we revert back to using that API?</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Thank you for your prompt attention to this issue.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">-Scott Marschalk</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
